article.headline: Belmont 79, Campbell 63
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Justin Hare scored 13 points as Belmont rolled past Campbell 79-63 Friday night in the Atlantic Sun Conference semifinals. Second-seeded Belmont (22-9) will face top-seeded East Tennessee State in Saturday's championship game and will be going for its second Atlantic Sun tournament championship in a row. The winner earns the conference's automatic bid to the NCAA tournament. Sixth-seeded Campbell finished 14-17. The Camels made the semifinals with an upset victory over No. 3 Jacksonville. Andrew Preston and Boomer Herndon scored 12 points apiece for the Bruins, who took advantage of their size to dominate inside. Henry Harris added 10. Hare was the Atlantic Sun tournaments most valuable player last year. Freshman Jonathan Rodriguez led Campbell with 16 points. Ledell Eackles and Eric Smith each added 10. Belmont led by 15 points in the first half but Campbell pulled to with six in the second half and had a chance to cut the deficit to four. But the Camels missed a layup and Matthew Dotson connected on a 3-point shot seconds later to put Belmont up 58-49 with 12:30 remaining. An 18-9 run gave the Bruins a cushion for the win.
